read my notes on cross_cmp_debian 
if you are using arch linux then this is for you with commands correspoinding to archlinux  to create tool chain of binutils-2.35 and gcc-10.2.0 for i686 
commands :-
export PREFIX="$HOME/opt/cross"
export TARGET=i686-elf
export PATH="$PREFIX/bin:$PATH"

sudo pacman -S  --needed gmp mpfr libmpc texinfo git make gcc

mkdir -p $HOME/src
cd $HOME/src

wget https://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/binutils/binutils-2.35.tar.xz
wget https://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/gcc/gcc-10.2.0/gcc-10.2.0.tar.xz

tar -xf binutils-2.35.tar.xz
tar -xf gcc-10.2.0.tar.xz

mkdir build-binutils
cd build-binutils

../binutils-2.35/configure --target=$TARGET --prefix="$PREFIX" --with-sysroot --disable-nls --disable-werror

make 
make install


cd $HOME/src
mkdir ./build-gcc
cd ./build-gcc
../gcc-10.2.0/configure --target=$TARGET --prefix="$PREFIX" --disable-nls --enable-languages=c --without-headers
make all-gcc
make all-target-libgcc
make install-gcc
make install-target-libgcc


after all running all these  check if it is properly installed by using commands

i686-elf-gcc --version
i686-elf-as --version

and 
which i686-elf-gcc 
	should return $HOME/opt/cross/*

i have explained all the commands in the cross_cmp_debian pdf,if you want you can ensure the legitimacy of packages using hashes i have not done it here.
